      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "univariate_event_peak_detector. Identifies the indices of prominent, sharp, transient events within a 1D numerical sequence. It operates by applying a series of signal processing steps\u2014typically including band-pass filtering, differentiation, non-linear amplification (e.g., squaring), and moving-average integration\u2014to create an energy envelope. Peaks are then detected within this envelope using an adaptive thresholding mechanism, isolating the locations of the key features.. Applications: Seismology: Detecting the precise arrival times of P-waves or S-waves in a seismogram to locate earthquake epicenters., Astrophysics: Identifying periodic dimming events in a star's light curve to detect transiting exoplanets., Audio Analysis: Locating percussive onsets, such as drum hits, within a digital audio waveform for rhythm extraction or automatic transcription.",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
    },
